<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-63-0380 </DOCNO><TEXT>Third, and last, part of a series of articles on large-scale energy storagesystems in the Netherlands. After a short introduction in which the historyof the research program is discussed, five different energy storage systemsare dealt with: Pump Accumulation Plant, also known as plan-Lievense;Underground Pump Accumulation Plant; Shell Pump Accumulation Plant (storagein salt domes); Compressed Air Accumulation Gasturbine Plant, also knownas the Huntorf-project; Adiabatic Compressed Air Storage System (storagein aquifers). Technical aspects, investment costs and location possibilitiesfor each of the five systems are highlighted. 2 figs., 4 refs., 5 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>